{
  "stem": "1603.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What I want you to know is that besides that we had to be afraid for our lives during the war, and for the past year almost or so, there were constant bombings in Hungary, just like in Germany.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, we're talking about 24-hour bombings with intervals for let's say there was four-hour bombing and two hours not bombing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was other three hours.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was just constantly going and never ending.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, that's how we lived.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We either could have died of the bombs or we could have been captured by the Germans and shot on the street.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So when we were living in an apartment on the third floor or fourth floor, and there was a constant air raid going, we couldn't go down to the air raid shelter to save our life, because we would have been caught there for that.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So also at a certain time, Alexander got us phony papers where our name became [INAUDIBLE], our family name instead of Fischl became [INAUDIBLE], which is a Hungarian name.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so my name was [INAUDIBLE] Peter, and I don't know the town, what it says the town we came from and so on and so on.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we had phony papers that we are Catholics and so on and so on, and we are refugees from the-- from territory where the Russians already occupied in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But thank god nobody ever examined the papers, because we would have been really then-- you know, if they would have pressed us, then we would have been real trouble.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There are things I recall that we lived in this Buda apartment, and the Germans had street cars-- street cars by the hundreds lined up in our neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was full with ammunition.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
